Arguments & Items
*****************

CLI Arguments
=============

Template:
          A=ALLOCATOR/S,E=EXTENDED/S

ALLOCATOR
     the allocator tool is online

EXTENDED
     more information about several memory types is shown

Menu Items
==========

'Project/About' - Shortcut: LAmiga-?
     the about, some interesting informations are shown :-D

'Project/Allocator' - Shortcut: LAmiga-A
     toggles allocator mode

'Project/Extended' - Shortcut: LAmiga-E
     toggles extended mode

'Project/Quit' - Shortcut: LAmiga-Q
     quit MUI-MemSnap

'Snap/New' - Shortcut: LAmiga-N
     a new snap is created, this means that a new snap line is inserted
     into the listview, the current values of the available mem are
     copied

'Snap/Remove' - Shortcut: LAmiga-R
     the active snap is removed, marked by the listview cursor

'Snap/Remove all' - Shortcut: LAmiga-M
     all snaps are removed

GUI Items
=========

Button 'New Snap' - Hotkey: N
     a new snap is created, this means that a new snap line is inserted
     into the listview, the current values of the available mem are
     copied

Rectangle at begin of each snap entry - DoubleClick
     removes the active snap

'Allocator' switch at the left side of Button 'New Snap' - Hotkey: A
     toggles allocator mode

'Extended' switch at the right side of Button 'New Snap' - Hotkey: E
     toggles allocator mode

Slider 'allocated ChipMem' - HotKey: C
     allocates ChipMem

Slider 'allocated FastMem' - HotKey: F
     allocates FastMem


